description: Programmatically create, access and manage Google Analytics entities such as accounts, properties, views, etc. Manage user permissions and import data.
steps: Go to Google Developers Console https://console.developers.google.com/
Select a project, or create a new one.
Press Continue to activate API key.
In the sidebar on the left, select Credentials
If your project has no API key for the server, create it now - Add credentials > API key > Server key
After receiving code from the user, please use getAccesToken block

blocks.name: getAccessToken
blocks.description: Exchange code for access token.

args.name: clientId
args.info: The client ID that you obtain from the API Console, as described in Obtain OAuth 2.0 credentials.

args.name: clientSecret
args.info: The client secret that you obtain from the API Console, as described in Obtain OAuth 2.0 credentials.

args.name: code
args.info: The authorization code that is returned from the initial request.

args.name: redirectUri
args.info: The URI that you specify in the API Console, as described in Set a redirect URI.

blocks.name: getAnalytics
blocks.description: Returns Analytics data for a view (profile).

args.name: accessToken
args.info: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

args.name: analyticsId
args.info: Unique table ID for retrieving Analytics data. Table ID is of the form ga:XXXX, where XXXX is the Analytics view (profile) ID. (string)

args.name: startDate
args.info: Start date for fetching Analytics data. Requests can specify a start date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD, or as a relative date (e.g., today, yesterday, or 7daysAgo). The default value is 7daysAgo.

args.name: endDate
args.info: End date for fetching Analytics data. Request can should specify an end date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD, or as a relative date (e.g., today, yesterday, or 7daysAgo). The default value is yesterday.

args.name: metrics
args.info: List of Analytics metrics.  E.g., 'ga:sessions,ga:pageviews'.

args.name: dimensions
args.info: List of Analytics dimensions. E.g., 'ga:browser,ga:city'.

args.name: filters
args.info: List of dimension or metric filters to be applied to Analytics data.

args.name: includeEmptyRows
args.info: The response will include empty rows if this parameter is set to true, the default is true

args.name: maxResults
args.info: The maximum number of entries to include in this feed.

args.name: samplingLevel
args.info: The desired sampling level.

args.name: segment
args.info: An Analytics segment to be applied to data.

args.name: sort
args.info: List of dimensions or metrics that determine the sort order for Analytics data.

args.name: startIndex
args.info: An index of the first entity to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

args.name: fields
args.info: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

args.info: A floating-point number between 0 and 1. Specifies the fraction of the traffic that participates in the experiment.
